1. Executive Summary
JetSet.AI is a React/TypeScript web application that transforms the traditionally fragmented travel planning experience into a seamless, intelligent, end-to-end journey. The existing frontend provides a polished dark-themed landing page built with Vite and currently integrates a third-party Botpress chatbot widget. This PRD defines the full product requirements to remove that chatbot dependency and replace it with a deeply integrated, API-driven planning engine delivering real-time flight fares, hotel recommendations, attraction opening hours, best-travel-season insights, emergency flight options, and AI-generated itineraries — all within one unified interface.

The redesigned product is organized around a single planning flow: the user provides their origin, destination, travel dates, trip duration, and budget — and JetSet.AI assembles a complete travel package with live data from best-in-class APIs, ranked by cost and quality.

2. Problem Statement
2.1 Current User Pain Points
•Travelers must juggle 5-10 separate apps (Skyscanner, Booking.com, Google Maps, TripAdvisor, Weather apps) to plan a single trip.
•Flight prices are volatile and opaque; finding the cheapest fare especially for emergencies requires constant manual monitoring.
•Seasonal travel intelligence (best months to visit, crowd levels, weather windows) is scattered across travel blogs with no personalization.
•Hotel discovery relative to key landmarks is manual and time-consuming with no budget calibration.
•Attraction opening hours are inconsistently maintained across the web and hard to aggregate into a single view.
•Day-by-day itinerary planning remains a manual, spreadsheet-driven exercise for most travelers.

2.2 Existing App Limitations
•The Botpress chatbot widget is a black box — it cannot render structured travel data like flight cards, hotel grids, or embedded maps.
•No persistent state: the chatbot conversation is lost on every page refresh.
•No real-time API integration: all data is static or hallucinated by the underlying LLM.
•No budget awareness or cost optimization logic built into any part of the current UI.

3. Goals & Success Metrics
3.1 Product Goals
1.Replace the Botpress chatbot with a native, structured planning interface.
2.Integrate live flight, hotel, attraction, and weather data via third-party APIs.
3.Deliver a complete trip plan within 30 seconds of user input via parallel API calls.
4.Enable emergency flight lookups for same-day or next-day travel at the cheapest available fare.
5.Surface best-season-to-travel recommendations calibrated to user budget and stated preferences.

