6. Feature Requirements
6.1 Trip Planning Wizard
The entry point of the application. Replaces the current static landing page hero section with an interactive multi-step form. All subsequent modules are triggered in parallel when the user submits this form.

Required Input Fields
•Origin city or airport with autocomplete (Google Places API)
•Destination city with autocomplete (Google Places API)
•Departure date via date picker, minimum selectable date is today
•Return date via date picker, conditional on one-way vs. round-trip toggle
•Trip duration in days, auto-calculated from dates or manually entered for flexible planning
•Total budget in USD via slider with preset tiers: Budget under $1,500, Mid-Range $1,500-5,000, Luxury above $5,000
•Number of travelers with separate adult and children counts
•Travel preference tags as a multi-select: Beach, Mountains, Cities, Culture, Adventure, Food

Behavior
•Real-time inline validation with clear error messages on each field
•3-step progress indicator: Destination, Dates & Budget, Preferences
•Plan My Trip CTA fires parallel API calls to all five data modules simultaneously
•Loading state shows per-module progress indicators as each API call resolves

6.2 Flight Search Module
Displays outbound and return flights in a card-based UI with complete airline, timing, and pricing details. Sorted by cheapest fare by default.

Flight Card Display
•Airline name and logo
•Departure and arrival airport codes, city names, and terminals where available
•Departure and arrival times in the local timezone of each city
•Total flight duration including layover time and layover city
•Number of stops with layover city name and connection duration
•Cabin class: Economy, Business, or First
•Price per person and total cost for all travelers combined
•Book on [Airline or Partner] deep-link button

Sorting and Filtering
•Sort by: Cheapest, Fastest, or Best (balanced score of price and duration)
•Filter by: maximum number of stops, preferred airline, departure time window, and maximum price

Recommended APIs
•Primary: Amadeus Flight Offers Search API (free tier: 2,000 requests/month, OAuth2 authentication)
•Alternative: Skyscanner Flights Live Prices API via RapidAPI
•Fallback: Google Flights results via SerpAPI

6.3 Emergency Flight Panel
A dedicated always-accessible panel for last-minute travel needs. Surfaces the three cheapest real-time available flights from the user's current or specified origin for same-day or next-day departure.

•Trigger: Emergency Flight button visible in the app header at all times regardless of current wizard step
•Inputs: current city (auto-detected via browser Geolocation API or manually entered), destination city, and travel date (Today or Tomorrow)
•Results: top 3 cheapest options sorted by total price ascending
•Each result shows: airline name, departure time, arrival time, total price, and number of seats remaining at that price
•Book Now button deep-links directly to the airline or OTA partner checkout page
•Target response time: 10 seconds or less
•Uses the same Amadeus API credentials as standard flight search, with date constrained to today or tomorrow

6.4 Hotel & Accommodation Finder
Surfaces hotels near the destination's key landmarks, pre-filtered by the user's budget tier, with an embedded Google Maps view showing property pin locations.

Hotel Card Display
•Hotel name, star rating, and aggregated user review score
•Walking or driving distance from city center or nearest top landmark
•Price per night and total cost for the full trip duration
•Thumbnail photo of the property
•Top 3 amenities highlighted: options include WiFi, Pool, Breakfast Included, Free Cancellation, Gym, Parking
•Availability status badge: Available, Limited Rooms, or Sold Out
•View on Booking.com or partner deep-link button

Filters
•Budget tier auto-applied from wizard: Budget under $80/night, Mid-Range $80-200, Luxury above $200
•Proximity radius slider: 1 km, 3 km, 5 km, or 10 km from selected landmark
•Star rating multi-select: 1 through 5 stars

Recommended APIs
•Primary: Booking.com Affiliate API or Hotels.com via RapidAPI
•Alternative: Amadeus Hotel Search API
•Map: Google Maps JavaScript API with interactive hotel pins

6.5 Best Season Advisor
Provides month-by-month travel intelligence for the destination, helping users choose the optimal travel window relative to their budget, weather preferences, and tolerance for crowds.

Display
•12-month calendar heat map with each month color-coded: Green for ideal, Yellow for acceptable, Red for avoid
•Per-month tooltip showing: average temperature range, rainfall or dry season status, crowd level estimate (Low, Medium, High, or Peak), and average flight price relative to the annual baseline
•You selected [Month] callout comparing the user's chosen travel dates to the identified optimal travel window
•Budget impact callout, for example: Traveling in August costs approximately 40% more in flights than April

Data Sources
•Weather history and forecasts: Open-Meteo API (free, no API key required) or WeatherAPI.com
•Month-by-month flight price index: Amadeus Flight Inspiration Search API
•Tourism seasonality context: supplemented by Claude AI synthesis using destination knowledge

6.6 Itinerary Generator
Produces a day-by-day itinerary incorporating real landmark data, current attraction opening hours from Google Places, admission cost estimates, and recommended visit durations.

Per-Day Card Requirements
•Day number and corresponding calendar date
•Morning, Afternoon, and Evening segments each containing 1-2 recommended activities
•Per activity: landmark or attraction name, category tag (Museum, Nature, Food, Shopping, or Nightlife), recommended visit duration, current opening hours, approximate admission cost, and Google Maps deep-link
•Lunch and dinner restaurant suggestions near each activity cluster
•Estimated daily spend covering activities and meals but excluding hotel and flight

Day Allocation Logic
•Trips 3 days or fewer: 2-3 major attractions per day, prioritized by user preference tags from the wizard
•Trips 4-7 days: balanced mix of iconic landmarks and off-the-beaten-path discoveries
•Trips over 7 days: includes day-trip suggestions to nearby cities or regions
•One designated flexibility day recommended for any trip of 5 or more days

Recommended APIs
•Google Places API: attraction details, photos, real opening hours, and user ratings
•Foursquare Places API: restaurant and nightlife recommendations
•Claude AI via Anthropic API: activity sequencing, narrative generation, and travel tips

6.7 AI Trip Summary (Claude Integration)
The final output module. Synthesizes all collected data into a human-readable trip brief rendered within the app. This fully replaces the Botpress chatbot widget removed in Phase 0.

•Input: all structured data from the five modules above — flights, hotels, season data, itinerary, and attraction hours
•Output: a 3-5 paragraph trip narrative covering highlights, practical travel tips, a budget breakdown, and packing suggestions based on destination weather
•Interactive follow-up: user can ask questions such as What if I extend by 2 days? or Find cheaper hotels and Claude refines specific modules in response
•Streaming enabled: Claude API called with streaming so text appears progressively rather than in a single delayed block
•Export: Download PDF button exports the complete plan as a formatted document
•Share: Copy Link generates a shareable URL with trip parameters encoded in the query string — no authentication required in v1

