7.1 API Key Management
•All API keys stored exclusively in environment variables and never committed to version control
•A lightweight backend proxy (Node.js/Express or Next.js API routes) is required to prevent key exposure in the client bundle
•Rate limiting middleware on the proxy to prevent API abuse from malicious or runaway clients
•Response caching: flights cached 5 minutes, hotel results 15 minutes, attraction hours 24 hours
•Graceful degradation: if any single API fails, that module shows an error card without blocking results from the other four modules

