9. User Flows
9.1 Standard Trip Planning Flow
6.User lands on the JetSet.AI homepage and sees the hero section with the Plan My Trip CTA
7.User fills the 3-step Trip Planning Wizard: Step 1 is Origin and Destination, Step 2 is Dates and Budget, Step 3 is Travel Preferences
8.User clicks Plan My Trip and all five module API calls fire in parallel simultaneously
9.Results Dashboard loads with animated skeleton placeholders that are progressively replaced by real data as each API resolves
10.User browses the Flights tab, views outbound and return options, applies sort and filter controls, and clicks through to book externally
11.User browses the Hotels tab, views options near landmarks sorted by budget tier, and interacts with the embedded map
12.User views the Best Season tab, reviews the 12-month heat map, and compares their chosen travel dates to the recommended optimal window
13.User views the Itinerary tab, reviews the day-by-day plan with attraction hours and meal suggestions, and adjusts preferences if desired
14.User reads the AI Trip Summary, asks follow-up refinement questions, and receives updated recommendations
15.User exports the full plan as a PDF or copies the shareable link

9.2 Emergency Flight Flow
16.User clicks the Emergency Flight button in the app header, which is visible at all times regardless of current step
17.The Emergency panel opens as a modal: user confirms or manually enters current city and destination
18.User selects travel date: Today or Tomorrow
19.System queries Amadeus for cheapest same-day or next-day fares within a 10-second target
20.Top 3 cheapest options are displayed with price, departure time, arrival time, and seats remaining
21.User clicks Book Now and is deep-linked to the airline or OTA booking page

10. Non-Functional Requirements
10.1 Performance
•Largest Contentful Paint: 2.5 seconds or less on a 4G connection
•Time to Interactive: 4 seconds or less
•Full trip plan response via parallel API calls: 30 seconds or less
•Emergency flight lookup: 10 seconds or less

10.2 Reliability
•Each API module must degrade gracefully — a failure in one shows an error card without blocking the others
•API request timeout: 15 seconds per call with one automatic retry on timeout
•Cached responses served if the live API is unavailable, with a data-age indicator badge

10.3 Security
•All API keys stored server-side only and never exposed in the frontend JavaScript bundle
•Backend proxy validates and sanitizes all user inputs before forwarding to third-party APIs
•HTTPS enforced in production (Vercel handles this automatically for all deployments)
•No personally identifiable information stored in v1

10.4 Accessibility
•WCAG 2.1 AA compliance — all interactive elements must be fully keyboard-navigable
•ARIA labels on all icon-only buttons including the Emergency Flight header button
•Minimum 4.5:1 color contrast ratio throughout (the existing dark theme requires minor color adjustments to be fully compliant)

10.5 Browser and Device Support
•Browsers: Chrome 100+, Firefox 100+, Safari 15+, Edge 100+
•Devices: Mobile 375px and above, Tablet 768px and above, Desktop 1024px and above
•All new components must use the responsive breakpoints already established in the existing index.css

